#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Azure Container Apps dynamic sessions sandbox provider.

This provider intentionally uses only Python's standard library. It talks to the
Azure Container Apps Sandbox data-plane REST API directly and obtains tokens via
`az account get-access-token`.

Provider configuration is profile-based JSON loaded from:

  $CONFIG_BASE/sandbox-providers/azure-sandbox/config.json

The config path can be overridden with `--config /path/to/config.json` for CLI
subcommands, or `AZURE_SANDBOX_CONFIG_PATH=/path/to/config.json` for any mode.

The provider receives the profile name from `azure-sandbox/<profile>` and looks
up `profiles[profile]` in that file. Example:

  {
    "profiles": {
      "default": {
        "azure": {
          "region": "eastus2",
          "subscription_id": "...",
          "resource_group": "...",
          "sandbox_group": "..."
        },
        "snapshot_id": "...",
        "oci_image": {
          "image": "ghcr.io/example/smol-agent:latest",
          "entrypoint": ["/bin/sh"],
          "cmd": ["-lc", "sleep infinity"]
        },
        "cwd": "/workspace",
        "sync_workspace": true,
        "value_providers": {
          "example_api_auth": {
            "command": ["sh", "-c", "printf 'Bearer example-token'"]
          }
        },
        "egress_policy": {
          "defaultAction": "Deny",
          "trafficInspection": "Full",
          "rules": [{
            "name": "example-api-auth",
            "match": {"host": "api.example.com", "path": "/v1/*", "methods": ["GET", "POST"]},
            "action": {"type": "Transform", "headers": [{"operation": "Set", "name": "Authorization", "value": "${value_providers.example_api_auth}"}]}
          }]
        }
      }
    }
  }

Set exactly one sandbox source in a real profile: `snapshot_id`, `disk_id`,
`preset`, or `oci_image`. `oci_image` is shown above only as an alternative to
`snapshot_id`; do not configure both in the same profile.

Auth tokens are retrieved from Azure CLI with `az account get-access-token`.
"""

